&lt;h3&gt;Shabbat HaChodesh&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shabbat HaChodesh is the fourth of the five special Shabbatot before Passover. In the special Torah reading for this Shabbat (Exodus 12:1-20), God instructs Moses and Aaron on how to observe the first Passover. The special Haftarah reading from Ezekiel discusses the observance of Passover in the Temple. These special readings are meant to draw our attention to the fact that Passover is approaching and to encourage us to begin our preparations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading Scroll #2&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exodus 12:1-20 (P 458, RP 409, WTC 363)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Aliyah&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Haftarah - Traditional&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
